commentPostTextItems.html: India win by 51 runs they level series 1-1.

Chasing 270, the openers started off well but Irfan Pathan picked up Imran Farhat in the 5th over and then came back in the 7th over of the innings to clean up Afridi and that double-blow put India on top.
With Afridi back in the hut, the bowlers started to take control of things, the spinners tightened the grip and Pakistan kept on losing wickets at regular intervals
Inzamam played like a champion, and his hard hitting tactics kept Pakistan in the hunt till the end but sadly he was 'run-out' at a crucial stage and that was the end of the chase.

Rahul Dravid gets the man of the match award for his glorious innings of 92 which helped India reach a big total, Inzamam-ul-Hag takes home the man of the series award for his exploits with the bat in both the matches
That's all we have for you today, hope you have enjoyed the coverage - until next time it's good bye from all of us here at Cricinfo.
